menu "SD Card"

    config SD_DISABLE_SDMMC
        bool "Disable SDMMC (use SPI-only mode)"
        default y
        help
            When enabled, the SD card driver skips SDMMC host probing entirely
            and falls back directly to SPI mode on every mount attempt.

            Useful when SDMMC is unavailable or is causing instability on your
            hardware revision. Toggle for SDMMC operation, which tries SDMMC
            1-bit first and falls back to SPI automatically.

endmenu
